cs.HC, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.VIS, cs.DL. 

The paper discusses the connections between data provenance and interactive visualizations, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. 

- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on adding interactions to visualizations and how users interact with them. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely, as provenance is often used in databases to track the origin and history of data. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possibility, as provenance can be used to track the sources of information in a visualization. 
- cs.VIS (Visualization and Computer Graphics) is also a possible category, as the paper discusses how interactions can be added to visualizations. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is less likely, but still possible, as provenance can be used to track the history of data in digital libraries.
